---

<Layout title="Cast & Staff | Firebird">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-black text-white pt-24">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="relative h-[20vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black to-black z-10"></div>
      <div class="relative z-20 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-[#bfae9e]">CAST & STAFF</h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cast Section -->
    <section class="px-4 md:px-8 mb-12">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <div class="space-y-16">
          <!-- Cast Member 1 -->
          <div id="en-kanami" class="cast-card group flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start justify-center p-8 bg-black/30 rounded-lg scroll-mt-32">
            <div class="w-full md:w-1/5">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 md:w-52 md:h-52 overflow-hidden rounded-full mx-auto">
                <Image
                  src={KANAMI}
                  class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-2xl mb-2">KANAMI</h3>
              <p class="text-[#bfae9e] mb-4">Planning, Production, Host<br>Firebird</p>
              <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-white leading-relaxed font-light">
                Born in Hiroshima Prefecture.<br>
                Started learning Japanese dance at the age of 2, later switched to jazz dance and classical ballet, and studied at the Rosella Hightower Ballet School in Cannes, France, from the age of 16.<br>
                During her studies, she encountered the Barre au Sol Kniaseff Method® and received direct instruction from Jacqueline, a beloved disciple of the founder, Boris Kniaseff.<br><br>
                Later, she studied at the Moscow State Bolshoi Ballet Academy and graduated (obtained a diploma).<br>
                After training with the Washington Ballet, she signed a contract with the Columbia Classical Ballet in the United States and was selected as the lead in "The Nutcracker" just two months after joining, performing the full act. Since then, she has signed contracts as a soloist with numerous European ballet companies.<br>
                <br>
                Currently, she regularly studies in Paris and conducts workshops in Europe, America, and Southeast Asia, as well as appearing on television and in magazines.<br>
                <br>
                Author of "Lying Down Core Training of Parisiennes: KANAMI's Barre au Sol" published by Nihon Bungeisha.
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mt-4">                
                <a href="https://www.instagram.com/kanami_f?igsh=MzhibWswejgyM2F4" target="_blank" aria-label="Instagram" class="text-white text-3xl hover:text-pink-300"><i class="fab fa-instagram"></i></a>
                <a href="https://kanamishiki.com/" target="_blank" aria-label="Website" class="text-white text-3xl hover:text-blue-300"><i class="fas fa-globe"></i></a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Cast Member 3 -->
          <div id="en-shota" class="cast-card group flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start justify-center p-8 bg-black/30 rounded-lg scroll-mt-32">
            <div class="w-full md:w-1/5">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 md:w-48 md:h-48 overflow-hidden rounded-full mx-auto">
                <Image
                  src={SHOTA}
                  class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-2xl mb-2">Shota Onodera</h3>
              <p class="text-[#bfae9e] mb-4">Prince Ivan</p>
              <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-white leading-relaxed font-light">
                Started ballet at the age of 6, inspired by ballet dancer Masaya Masutake.<br>
                Studied under Kimura Kimika, Saito Yukari, and Nikolai Fyodorov from the age of 12, and under Sato Yuji from the age of 15.<br>
                The following year, he studied at the Russian State Perm Ballet School, where he received a special award at the Perm Ballet Competition during his studies.<br>
                In 2017, he moved to the Rudolf Nureyev Memorial Russian State Ballet.<br>
                He performs in Russia, America, and various parts of Europe.<br>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Cast Member 2 -->
