              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-2xl mb-2">Erica</h3>
              <p class="text-[#bfae9e] mb-4">Princess Tsarevna</p>
              <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-white leading-relaxed font-light">
                Started jazz dance at Musical Theatre STEPS at the age of 4, and later switched to classical ballet after rhythmic gymnastics and tap dance.<br>
                Studied under Ikemoto Emiko and Miyagi Noboru. Studied contemporary dance under Ishihara Kanji.<br>
                Studied at the German National Mannheim Ballet Academy from the age of 16.<br>
                Later, transferred to the Berlin State Ballet School and graduated.<br>
                Gained stage experience in ballet companies across Europe before returning to Japan.<br>
                Currently, she conducts workshops nationwide and in New York, teaching ballet, training, and the Barre au Sol Kniaseff Method® to children and adults.<br>
                She travels to France several times a year to receive training in the Barre au Sol Kniaseff Method®.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

