              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Cast Member 5 -->
          <div id="en-fedor" class="cast-card group flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start justify-center p-8 bg-black/30 rounded-lg scroll-mt-32">
            <div class="w-full md:w-1/5">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 md:w-48 md:h-48 overflow-hidden rounded-full mx-auto">
                <Image
                  src={MURASHOV}
                  class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="w-full md:w-2/3 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-2xl mb-2">Fedor Murashov</h3>
              <p class="text-[#bfae9e] mb-4">Choreographer</p>
              <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-white leading-relaxed font-light">
                Graduated from the Vaganova Ballet Academy in 2001 with a bachelor's degree.<br>
                Active at the Mariinsky Theatre from 2001 to 2022. Graduated from the Russian State Institute of Performing Arts in 2014, obtaining a master's degree in Theatre Management.<br>Appointed as the Deputy Artistic Director of the Ballet Department at the Yekaterinburg State Opera and Ballet Theatre in 2017.<br>Started studying at the Vaganova Ballet Academy's Faculty of Education (master's program) in 2020.<br>Worked as a lecturer at the St. Petersburg Eifman Ballet Academy from 2020 to 2022.<br>From 2019 to 2022, served as a judge and lecturer for the Vaganova Master Classes at the Japan International Ballet Festival held in Kawasaki City, and in 2022, worked as an assistant to Yuri Burlyaka, the choreographer of "Esmeralda" for the Japan Ballet Association. Currently based in Japan, working as a lecturer.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Cast Member 6 -->
          <div id="en-joseph" class="cast-card group flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start justify-center p-8 bg-black/30 rounded-lg scroll-mt-32">
            <div class="w-full md:w-1/5">
